<L>__{interior gas station men's room day}
<A>__{bobby removes his jacket and lays it on top of the waste container. he moves to the wash basin and stands a moment, gazing absently down at it, his mind searching for that inward oblivion in which nothing much is demanded, nothing much felt. then, leaning over and placing his hands on the rim of the basin... ... he lifts his gaze to the mirror and, after minutely perusing the features of his face, looks into his own eyes as he had into his fathers, silently beseeching them for guidance.}
